Reentrant Lock
--------------
- Locks are explicit where as synchronized is also nothing but lock is implicit
- Locks allow locking / unlocking in any scope and in any order - you lock in any method an unlock in other method
- Ability to tryLock and tryLock(timeout) - few extra method

Reentrant lock allows to call lock method multiple times on the same object.of course lock call must match with unlock call.
consider the scenario when your method calls recursively.Let say thread t1 has the lock and again reentering the same block which
it has the access. that is why is called as reentrant lock.it will acquired the lock again since it is already a owner of the lock.
behind the scene it hold count(getHoldCount()) gets incremented.

lock = new ReentrantLock(true) The reentrant lock becomes a fair lock. Let say there are 4 thread which wants to acquire a lock.
and Thread t1 arrives earlier and acquire the lock. In this case t1 gets the lock and other three thread will get into wait state.
In the wait state it will put into wait queue.Once Thread t1 calls the unlock method.it release the lock and any of the thread will
get a chance to acquire the lock. Since, thread t2 waited to longest for acquiring the lock. So, Reentrant Lock will guarantee that
thread t2 will get the chance to acquire among t3 and t4 thread. so it is first come first serve basis. By default reentrant lock are unfair.

              Advantage                     Disadvantage
Fair lock   - Equal chance for all thread   - Slower
Unfair lock - Faster(more throughput)       - possible thread starvation
Throughput - the rate at which something is processed.

