Atomic vs Volatile
------------------
Volatile is used for visibility problem and when we have compound operation which we wanted to do atomically.
Typically volatiles are used for flags generally for boolean or if we are setting the value directly without
checking the initial or the previous value of that we can use the volatile.
AtomicInteger and AtomicLong used for maintaining counters which are updated by multiple threads.
AtomicReference typically used for caches(building new cache in background and replacing dynamically) and non-blocking algorithm
-- Reason for atomic -----
Because are cpu has multiple cores or because we can never be sure about the jvm scheduling our threads it is possible
that instructions of these two threads are interleaved so the read operation of thread 1 is
followed by read operation by thread 2.

